BootInfoS

This script collects and displays key system information like CPU usage, memory stats, disk space, uptime, and top memory-consuming processes.

Features

- CPU usage snapshot
- RAM and swap info in MB
- Disk space of `/` in human-readable format
- Logged-in users count
- Uptime display
- Top 10 memory-consuming processes

1. Clone the repo or copy the script:

git clone https://github.com/your-username/BootInfoS.git

cd BootInfoS

2. Make the script executable:

chmod +x sysinfo.bash

3. Run the script:

./sysinfo.bash

4. To run this every time you open a new terminal, add this line to the end of your ~/.bashrc file:

~/BootInfoS/sysinfo.bash

5. Then apply the changes

source ~/.bashrc
